    <!-- 
Some Basic Tags-
    ^1) label:
          &Attributes:
          *1)for: 
          It is used to associate label with input element, 
          Input element should have some id which will be used in for attribute of label element for connecting a label with an input.
          
    ^2) input:
          -Attributes:
           *1)id: 
           It is used to assign some value to an 'input' by which we can set connection between 'label' and 'input' using same "id" value in "for" attribute in Label.
           
           *2)type: 
           It is used to specify the type/datatype of input.
            ?text: 
             
            ?password:
             
            ?email:
          
            ?number:
             
            ?radio:
             It is used to take radio input from user.
             We can also develop the method to only one radio button can be selected at a time(Check Form-2).
             
            ?checkbox:
             It is used to take checkbox input from user. We can select multiple checkboxes at a time.
            
            ? tel:
&------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
            ! Not Important 
            ?date:

            ?time:

            ?local:

            ?date-time local:

            ?week:
            
            ?month:

            ?color:

            ?file:

            ?image:
                 We have to also mention src here.
            
            ?search:

            ?range:
               By default, range will take from value 0 to 100. But we can change it with min and max attributes.

            ? url:
&------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    ! For type="number", "range" or "datetime" types(type="date", type="month", type="week", type="time", type="datetime-local")
            
                        ~6)  step:
                           Purpose: Specifies the legal number intervals for the input field. For example, step="2" for a number input means only even numbers (if the min is even) or odd numbers (if the min is odd) are valid.
                           For date/time inputs, it specifies the increment.
            
                        ~7)  min:
                           Purpose: Specifies the minimum value that is allowed for the input field.
            
                        ~8)  max:
                           Purpose: Specifies the maximum value that is allowed for the input field.

    ! For type=text or type= anything (we have to check) we have some more attributes.
                        ~9) minlength:
                           Purpose: Specifies the minimum number of characters a user must enter.
                              Used with these types: text, email, search, url, tel, password.
            
                        ~10) maxlength:
                           Purpose: Specifies the maximum number of characters a user can enter.
                              Used with these types: text, email, search, url, tel, password.
            
            
                        ~11) size:
                           Purpose: Specifies the visual width of the input field in characters. It's a visual hint, not a strict character limit (that's maxlength).
                              Used with these types: text, email, search, url, tel, password.
&------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------           

            *3)name:
                    It is used to specify the varible name of the input element. 
                    After submitting the form, the data will be saved in this variable in the URL (in case of no backend) or in the backend (in case of backend).
                    
            *4)value:
                    It is used to specify the default value of the input element.
                    It tells what value a particular input will take if the value is not provided by the user. 
                       ?default value:
                    It is used to specify the default value of the input element.
                    
            *5)placeholder:
                    It is used to specify a short hint that describes the expected value of the input field.
            
 ^3) textarea:
         Input tag is for single line input,but text area is used for multi line input.
         &Attributes:
         *1) name:
         *2) id:
         *3) rows:
         *4) cols:

  ^4) button:
           -Attributes:
           *1)type: It is used to specify the type of button.
                 By default ,type of button is Submit.
              ?reset:  
             It will clear the data without refreshing the page
              ?submit:
             It will submit the data to the server and also refresh the page.
                
-->               
